(this article is about the bridge in london, england. for the bridge in manchester, england, see blackfriars bridge, manchester. for the bridge in london, ontario, see blackfriars street bridge. for the british silent film, see blackfriars bridge (film).) blackfriars bridge is a road and foot traffic bridge over the river thames in london, between waterloo bridge and blackfriars railway bridge, carrying the a201 road. the north end is near the inns of court and temple church, along with blackfriars station. the south end is near the tate modern art gallery and the oxo tower.